; maize-150: instruction-path typo discipline preserved after the GAP 3
; data-context relaxation. `undefinedtypo` is used as a CP instruction-operand
; SOURCE, which routes through the shared obj_emit_label_ref helper (NOT a CALL,
; which uses write_label, and NOT a DREF/data initializer, which populates
; obj_data_refs). It is neither defined in this translation unit nor declared
; EXTERN, so `mazm -c` must still fatal with the strict maize-71 diagnostic. This
; proves the data-context obj_data_refs auto-EXTERN did NOT relax the instruction
; path; a silent SHN_UNDEF auto-import here would be a regression.

SECTION CODE

GLOBAL _start

_start:
    CP undefinedtypo R0        ; undefined, undeclared instruction source: must reject
    HALT
